## 4. Risk Calculation Reference

### Likelihood Scale (X-Axis)

| Score | Label | Approx. Probability | Rationale |
|--:|---|---|---|
| 1 | Very Unlikely | < 10% | Theoretically possible; very low historical base rate |
| 3 | Somewhat Unlikely | 10–30% | Plausible but requires significant triggering event |
| 5 | 50-50 Possibility | ~50% | Roughly equal chance; e.g., cybersecurity breach given known AWS exposure rates |
| 7 | Somewhat Likely | 60–80% | More likely than not without specific intervention |
| 9 | Very Likely | ≥ 80% | Near-certain given current conditions; e.g., capital costs, cost-of-inaction |

### Impact Scale (Y-Axis)

| Score | Label | Financial Range | Amazon-Specific Anchor |
|--:|---|---|---|
| 1 | Very Low | < $1M | Manageable within operating budget |
| 2 | Low | $1M–$10M | Minor; contained without executive escalation |
| 4 | Moderate | $10M–$100M | Noticeable; manageable with coordinated response |
| 6 | High | $100M–$500M | Significant; CCPA $7,500/violation × 100M+ customers |
| 8 | Very High | $500M–$5B | Major; $400M–$1.36B annual savings at stake |
| 9 | Extreme | $5B+ | Existential; EU AI Act 7% of $716.9B FY2025 = ~$50.2B |

### Severity Thresholds & Treatment Protocol

| Severity | Score | Color | Action Protocol |
|---|---|---|---|
| VERY HIGH | ≥ 54 | Red | Board-level escalation; immediate treatment plan with named owner and deadline |
| HIGH | 40–53 | Orange | Executive action; active mitigation; monthly KRI review |
| MODERATE | 18–39 | Yellow | Monitor; assign owner; quarterly review; escalate if KRI threshold breached |
| LOW | < 18 | Green | Accept with documented residual risk; annual review |
